astic instability or turbulence in the microfluidics will facilitate mixing enhancement and potential heat transfer enhancement.13 In addition, the nonlinearity required for the operation of logic microfluidic system derives from the use of viscoelastic fluid with nonlinear physical properties25 and the flow state is often related to elastic instability and turbulence. The rest of this paper is organized as follows. First, the theoretical background of viscoelastic fluid flow is introduced, including governing equations and important dimensionless parameters. Then, the basic characteristics of elastic instability and elastic turbulence of viscoelastic fluids in micro-scale flows are presented. Subsequently, some specific applications based on the nonlinearity of viscoelastic fluid in microfluidics are summarized. Finally, the prospects in these fields and new possible applications with viscoelastic fluid are summarized, respectively.
