Logic microfluidic circuit
Fluid circuit utilizes fluid components to achieve similar functions as electronic circuit components. Compared with electronic circuits, fluid circuits are more suitable for the engineering applications that require anti-electromagnetic interference and antiionizing radiation. The nonlinearity of flow is the key requirement.25 Although fluid circuits appeared earlier, due to the technical requirements of flow nonlinearity, Re number of the flows in early fluid circuits was generally large, which makes the miniaturization and integration extremely difficult to realize. An idea to solve this problem is to use viscoelastic fluid as working fluid, and then the elastic nonlinearity can be introduced to meet the requirement of nonlinearity of fluid circuit. Some other methods can also introduce nonlinearity of flows, such as two-phase flow,89 and chemical reaction materials.90 However, they are more complex and require more active components than the method of using single-phase viscoelastic fluid as working fluid. Specific microfluidic functionalities can be realized via changing the structural unit, topological structure, physical properties of working fluid and excitation signal of the system. A few of microfluidic circuits have been proposed, including flux stabilizer,25 bistable flip-flops25 and rectifiers,91 while other functional microfluidic components have not been
reported yet, let alone complex fluid control circuit systems. The development of microfluidic circuit with viscoelastic fluid is still relatively slow as a result of the following reasons: (1) complex flow mechanism of viscoelastic fluid itself; (2) a variety of random external excitation signals; and (3) difficult component manufacture and design. This section reviews several logic microfluidic circuits that have been well invented.
Flux stabilizer. Groisman et al. fulfilled a type of flux stabilizer25 that consists of 46 identical semi-elliptic geometric segments (Figure 12(a)). In this device, the time-reversal symmetry was broken for low-Re polymer fluids flow after a critical Wi, corresponding to a transition point of flow rate. The relationship of flow rate Q and pressure drop per segment ( P) was roughly linear prior to the threshold but non-linearly after this transition point, in which the flow rate increases much slower than that in the approximately linear region. This plateau region of flow rate may last as P ranges over a wide range. The contribution to the plateau is due to the rapidly increasing elastic stress, which provides high resistance. Components with such resistance characteristic can realize nonlinear resistor or variable resistor as well as piecewise linear resistor excluding some local nonlinear intervals. Analogous to electronic constant-current source, in the high resistance range, the nonlinear resistor’s flow rate is insensitive to the change of resistance, which can be regarded as a constant current source or flux stabilizer to a certain extent. In contrast, for the Newtonian fluid flow in this device, the flow rate is proportional to the pressure drop per segment and the characteristic of flow resistance is linear.
