Conclusions and outlook
The elastic nonlinearity is a unique property of viscoelastic fluids flows. In micro-scale flows dominated by elasticity, elastic instability and elastic turbulence can greatly promote mixing and heat transfer. Through elaborate design of microchannel shape and fluid physical property selection, logic microfluidic components that are similar to electronic counterparts can be obtained and integrated into a logic microfluidic system with specific functions. This has important applications in situations where anti-electromagnetic interference and anti-ionizing radiation are extremely demanded. Particle manipulation is another important application of viscoelastic fluids. The viscoelastic fluid not only plays the role of dissolving particles, but also provides an additional elastic force to manipulate them. In this review, the effect of external force is not taken into consideration, but viscoelastic fluid alone is introduced as working fluid. This can eliminate the need to introduce active components and external energy (excluding the energy used to drive fluid flow), simplify the design of channel structure, and reduce the complexity of the system.
To sum up, in the regime of Re 0 and Wi > 1, viscoelastic fluid takes advantages over Newtonian fluid as follows: (1) mass and heat transfer enhancement; (2) offering a nonlinear source, i.e. elastic nonlinearity, that enables to realize a logic functionality that is analogous to its counterpart, electronic components; (3) enriching the ways of manipulating particles. To get more insights into viscoelastic fluid flows in microfluidics, both experimental and numerical methods need to be further improved. In terms of experiment, accurate measuring techniques especially for the information of microstructures behavior, such as macromolecular structural deformation, elastic stress field, needs to be developed. As for numerical techniques, development of robust multi-scale-and-multiphysical field coupling methods for viscoelastic fluid flows will be a necessity to explore the potential of viscoelastic fluids to design various novel and efficient microfluidic devices. With the improvement and development of the above-mentioned two aspects, the viscoelastic fluid will be studied more thoroughly and its application will be more indispensable and extensive. With the increasing needs from the biology, medicine, chemistry and microelectromechanical fields, microfluidics based on viscoelastic fluid as working fluid have drawn great attention. In addition to the above-mentioned applications, viscoelastic fluid can be potentially exploited as the media in energy storage components, where the energy conversion can be realized between elastic energy and other types of energy. This may be a promising trend from the energy conservation prospective.
